Project: D&D AI Application
Type: Web Application
Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Prisma ORM, OpenAI API
Database: SQLite (dev), PostgreSQL (prod)
Package Manager: npm
Node Version: 18+

Key Conventions:
- Use @ path alias for imports (@/components, @/lib, @/types)
- Strict TypeScript mode enabled
- App directory structure (not pages)
- Server Components by default, Client Components marked with 'use client'
- Tailwind CSS for all styling (no CSS modules)
- Prisma for all database operations
- Environment variables prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ for client-side

Project Structure Reference: ./docs/dnd-project-spec.md

Current Phase: Initial Setup
Style Guide:
- Components use PascalCase
- Utilities use camelCase  
- Types/Interfaces use PascalCase with 'I' or 'T' prefix optional
- API routes follow RESTful conventions

D&D Specific:
- Strict D&D 5e rules compliance
- All game mechanics must be accurate to official rules
- Use official terminology (e.g., "Armor Class" not "Defense")
